    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 MODEL - HEATER AND AIR CONDITIONER (CAB)</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsection id="s08282" division="truck" formnum="CTS-5304-12" date="04/03/2000">
        <title>HEATER AND AIR CONDITIONER (CAB)</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>9800
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>11/01/1998</startdate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
            <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
            <para>The heater/air conditioning system has a blower motor circuit and a compressor control circuit. The
                compressor control circuit is tied to the blower motor circuit which can be set to off, low, medium or
                high speed to circulate heat or cooling throughout the cab.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
